<h2 id="Thematic-Roles-and-Primitive-Actions">Thematic Roles and Primitive Actions<a class="anchor-link" href="#Thematic-Roles-and-Primitive-Actions">Â¶</a></h2><ul>
<li>If a concept that comes before the verb is animate, put that as agent</li>
<li>If a concept that comes after the verb is inanimate, put that as object</li>
<li>These are called <strong>structured knowledge representations</strong>. </li>
</ul>
<p><img alt="2019-06-30_15h45_29.png" src="data:image/png;base64, "/></p>
<h3 id="Example">Example<a class="anchor-link" href="#Example">Â¶</a></h3><p><img alt="2019-06-30_15h48_02.png" src="data:image/png;base64, "/></p>
<p>Note how rules and frames are working together (there is a rule on how to decide agent from sentence, for example). Also lexical, syntactic, semantic all working together here.</p>
<p>How do we know? Because we could ask questions. Who had the book?  And all answers could come from frame.</p>
